<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14160">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Scuba%20Diving.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2557">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2557 mb-requirement-id-2558">
        (a) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while scuba diving, including hypothermia, hyperventilation,
        squeezes, decompression illness, nitrogen narcosis, motion sickness,
        fatigue, overexertion, heat reactions, dehydration, injuries by aquatic
        life, and cuts and scrapes. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qFWDTNuS0Xo" target="_blank"
          >What Is Hypothermia? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c-BSo8OknNc" target="_blank"
          >What Are the Bends in Scuba Diving? Decompression Sickness Explained
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Y8CKkbgIahk" target="_blank"
          >How To Relieve Cramps While Scuba Diving (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7PLnYgUHOP4" target="_blank"
          >Diving With Anxiety | Tips for Staying Calm &amp; Confident at Depth!
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://dan.org/safety-prevention/diver-safety/divers-blog/seasickness-prevention-and-treatment/"
          target="_blank"
          >Seasickness Prevention and Treatment (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-nZHTqSaJ0c" target="_blank"
          >What Is Nitrogen Narcosis and How Do You Get It? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2557 mb-requirement-id-2562">
        (b) Identify the conditions that must exist before performing CPR on a
        person, and explain how to recognize such conditions. Demonstrate the
        proper technique for performing CPR using a training device approved by
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6eRwgM2Pa4o" target="_blank"
          >How To Perform Hands-Only CPR (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2565">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Before completing requirements 3 through 6, earn the Swimming merit badge.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://www.scouting.org/merit-badges/swimming/" target="_blank"
        >Swimming Merit Badge (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2567">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Discuss the Scuba Diver's Code with your counselor, and explain the
      importance of each guideline to a scuba diver's safety. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a
        href="https://www.divessi.com/en/training/responsible-diver-code-scuba"
        target="_blank"
        >Scuba School International Divers Code (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2568">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Earn an Open Water Diver Certification from a scuba organization
      recognized by the Scouting America scuba policy. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/PCcTAS53Inc" target="_blank"
        >How To Get Scuba Certified (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2569">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Explain what an ecosystem is, and describe four aquatic ecosystems a diver
      might experience. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/vINK9ujrRwM" target="_blank"
        >Aquatic Ecosystems (Characteristics, Types and Examples) (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2570">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Find out about three career opportunities in the scuba industry. Pick one
      and find out the education, training, and experience required for this
      profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this
      profession might interest you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TGj1ua6SWts" target="_blank"
        >Top 5 Jobs in the Commercial Diving Industry (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/S2yhU1KHoHM" target="_blank"
        >Navy Diver (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TAB0-ZQ9cUU" target="_blank"
        >Navy Medical Deep Sea Diving Technician—DMT (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/h1VFsl_JplQ" target="_blank"
        >5 Types of Diving Job (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/MHObp9RUV-w" target="_blank"
        >Dream Job: A Day in the Life of Our Divers by Aquarium Love Stories
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
